headline: Morgan Stanley Sees a Compelling Entry Point in These 2 Cloud Stocks
summary: The modern cloud computing infrastructure has been expanding over the past two decades, and what was once a convenient backup system has now become the backbone of the digital world. Cloud computing lets subscribers – at all levels, from individuals to large enterprises – tap into the speed and flexibility of high-end data centers, without having to build or maintain the physical servers. Seen from the other side, cloud computing lets server operators run their systems with a minimum of downtime
